      <div class="stage-card">
        <div class="tag">After go-live</div>
        <p class="q">We've just gone live and issues are surfacing faster than we can resolve them.</p>
        <a class="go" href="#how-we-work">See hypercare →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="services" id="how-we-work">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">What we do</div>
      <h2>A mini-PMO for payroll and HR system change</h2>
      <p class="lead">One point of accountability from the moment a change is proposed to the moment it's stable in production.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="svc-table">
      <div class="svc-row">
        <div class="name"><span class="idx">01</span>Change intake</div>
        <div class="outcome">Clear scope and impact assessment</div>
      </div>
      <div class="svc-row">
        <div class="name"><span class="idx">02</span>Vendor coordination</div>
        <div class="outcome">Single point of contact across every vendor</div>
      </div>
      <div class="svc-row">
        <div class="name"><span class="idx">03</span>Test management</div>
        <div class="outcome">Fewer payroll defects at go-live</div>
      </div>
      <div class="svc-row">
        <div class="name"><span class="idx">04</span>Cutover planning</div>
        <div class="outcome">On-time, controlled go-live</div>
      </div>
      <div class="svc-row">
        <div class="name"><span class="idx">05</span>Hypercare</div>
        <div class="outcome">Rapid issue resolution after release</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="playbook" id="playbook">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">How we work</div>
      <h2>A repeatable operating system, not ad hoc consulting</h2>
      <p class="lead">Every engagement runs on the same four artifacts — built and refined on real payroll change, not written for a proposal.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tpl-grid">
      <div class="tpl-card">
        <div class="letter">A</div>
        <h3>Payroll change intake form</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Business reason</li>
          <li>Legal &amp; compliance impact</li>
          <li>Payroll countries affected</li>
          <li>Upstream / downstream systems</li>
          <li>Required effective date</li>
          <li>Rollback requirements</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="tpl-card">
        <div class="letter">B</div>
        <h3>Impact assessment template</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Configuration changes</li>
          <li>Interface changes</li>
          <li>Reporting changes</li>
          <li>Testing scope</li>
          <li>Risk rating — low / medium / high</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="tpl-card">
        <div class="letter">C</div>
        <h3>Test pack</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Parallel payroll</li>
          <li>Retro calculations</li>
          <li>New joiner / leaver scenarios</li>
          <li>Overtime &amp; allowance cases</li>
          <li>Statutory calculations</li>
          <li>GL posting validation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="tpl-card">
        <div class="letter">D</div>
        <h3>Cutover checklist</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Config migrated</li>
          <li>Interfaces enabled</li>
          <li>Security validated</li>
          <li>Payroll control totals signed off</li>
          <li>Rollback plan approved</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="fit" id="fit">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head" style="text-align:left; margin-bottom:40px;">
      <div class="eyebrow">Who this is for</div>
      <h2>Built for the person who owns the change</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="fit-grid">
      <div class="fit-col">
        <h3>A good fit if</h3>
        <ul class="fit-list yes">
          <li>You own or influence a payroll, HRIS or workforce system change — Head of Payroll, Payroll Director, Head of HR Systems, HR Transformation Lead, or Director of People Operations</li>
          <li>Your organisation has roughly 500–5,000 employees</li>
          <li>You have a change on the roadmap — new system, vendor switch, M&amp;A payroll harmonisation, or multi-country consolidation</li>
          <li>You want an accountable delivery partner, not another vendor to manage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="fit-col">
        <h3>Probably not yet a fit if</h3>
        <ul class="fit-list no">
          <li>You're looking for a payroll bureau to run payroll on an ongoing basis</li>
          <li>You need enterprise-wide strategy consulting or target operating model design</li>
          <li>You're a very small business without a dedicated payroll or HR systems function</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about" id="about">
  <div class="wrap about-grid">
    <div class="avatar">MK</div>
    <div>
      <div class="role">Co-Founder</div>
      <h2>Michal Kempinski</h2>
      <p>Northbound is built and run out of a background in technical account management and operational process improvement inside payroll and workforce technology, currently at Wagestream.</p>
      <p>The approach here didn't start as a pitch deck. It started as an internal payroll change delivery function — the same intake, testing and cutover discipline described in the playbook above — refined on real changes before being offered externally.</p>
