    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about" id="about">
  <div class="wrap about-grid">
    <div class="avatar">FL</div>
    <div>
      <div class="role">Co-Founder</div>
      <h2>Faye Levy</h2>
      <p>Northbound is built and run out of a background in technical account management and operational process improvement inside payroll and workforce technology, currently at Wagestream.</p>
      <p>The approach here didn't start as a pitch deck. It started as an internal payroll change delivery function — the same intake, testing and cutover discipline described in the playbook above — refined on real changes before being offered externally.</p>
      <p>We're an early-stage, hands-on practice. We won't tell you we've run hundreds of go-lives — we haven't, yet. What we can offer is senior attention on every engagement and a delivery method that's already been tested where it counts.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Questions</div>
      <h2>Frequently asked</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details>
        <summary>Are you a new practice? How much experience do you have?</summary>
        <p>Northbound is an early-stage practice. It grew out of hands-on payroll change delivery work inside Wagestream, not years of consultancy trading. If you need a large bench of consultants with a decade of case studies, we're probably not the right fit yet. If you want senior, hands-on attention from someone who has actually run this work, we might be.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do you run our payroll for us, or support the change?</summary>
        <p>We're a change delivery partner, not a payroll bureau. We don't process your payroll on an ongoing basis — we help you scope, test, cut over and stabilise a change to your payroll or HR systems, then hand back a working, documented process.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do you handle UK payroll compliance — HMRC, RTI, BACS, auto-enrolment?</summary>
        <p>Our test packs and cutover checklists are built around statutory calculation testing, RTI (FPS/EPS) readiness, BACS validation and pension auto-enrolment settings, alongside GL posting and control total sign-off, so compliance checks are part of the delivery method rather than an afterthought.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can you help if we're already mid-project and things are going wrong?</summary>
        <p>Yes. Bringing in structured intake, an honest impact assessment and a proper test pack partway through a struggling implementation is one of the most common ways this kind of support gets used. We can join at any stage, not just at the start.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What does this cost?</summary>
        <p>It depends on the scope of the change. We start with a free 30-minute conversation to understand what's coming up, then propose a fixed-fee scope for the engagement — no open-ended day-rate billing without a defined outcome.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Which payroll or HR systems do you work with?</summary>
        <p>We work with whatever's relevant to your change rather than claiming coverage across every platform on the market. Tell us your systems on the first call and we'll tell you honestly whether we're the right fit.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

